-- Mexico Stocks: OHL Mexico, Penoles, Genomma Lab Share Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-05-11T21:37:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/mexico-stocks-ohl-mexico-penoles-genomma-lab-share-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index fell 0.7 percent to 38,888.79.  Genomma Lab Internacional SAB (LABB)  , the Mexican
producer of over-the-counter drugs, climbed 1.5 percent to 26.04
pesos. The shares have rallied 9.7 percent since May 2, the day
before it announced it was withdrawing a bid to buy Prestige
Brands Holdings Inc., the maker of Comet household cleanser.  OHL Mexico SAB (OHLMEX*)  , the Mexican unit of Spanish
construction company Obrascon Huarte Lain SA, tumbled 7.4
percent to 18.65 pesos. OHL Mexico said yesterday in a filing to
Mexico’s stock exchange that the state of Puebla voided a
concession with its unit Autovias Concesionadas OHL.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), a Mexican miner of
silver and gold, fell 2.4 percent to 556.36 pesos. The metals’
futures slipped on concern  Europe ’s debt crisis is deepening.  To contact the reporter on this story:
